OL,3,CWhose responsibility is pollution in
OL,4,CUK seas, and how is it cleaned up?
OL,6,FAccording to HM Coastguard, that
OL,7,Fincludes lumps of wax washed onto a
OL,8,Fbeach; plastics; timber, or other
OL,9,Fsubstances lost from shipping
OL,10,Fcontainers, including oil and fuel.
OL,12,FWhose job is it to respond to
OL,13,Fpollution?
OL,15,FThe UK is responsible for responding
OL,16,Fto any pollution within its Exclusive
OL,17,FEconomic Zone, which reaches up to 200
OL,18,Fnautical miles from land. HM
OL,19,FCoastguard is the first port of call
OL,20,Ffor incidents of pollution.
