OL,3,CWhose responsibility is pollution in
OL,4,CUK seas, and how is it cleaned up?
OL,6,FThe first job of the Coastguard once
OL,7,Fpollution is reported is to find its
OL,8,Fsource. Key questions would be: What's
OL,9,Fbeen spilled? Where will it go? What
OL,10,Fdamage will it cause?
OL,12,FSome of those questions are answered
OL,13,Fby using computer models.
OL,15,FThe most important goal of the
OL,16,FCoastguard is to stop the pollution
OL,17,Fspreading and reaching land, where it
OL,18,Fcan cause further damage to public
OL,19,Fhealth, the environment, communities
OL,20,Fand the economy.
