OL,3,CWhose responsibility is pollution in
OL,4,CUK seas, and how is it cleaned up?
OL,6,FHM Coastguard keeps a 24-hour watch,
OL,7,Fmonitoring shipping traffic in order
OL,8,Fto avoid dangerous situations and can,
OL,9,Fwhere necessary, assist vessels that
OL,10,Fmight be in trouble.
OL,12,FThey can send out support vessels when
OL,13,Fneeded and may use the UK's emergency
OL,14,Ftowing vessel, the Ievoli Black, based
OL,15,Fin the north of Scotland. By catching
OL,16,Fproblems early, escalation can be
OL,17,Favoided and the risk of a pollution
OL,18,Fproblem reduced.
